Subject: shift rod coupler

Gerald,

I have found in my last 2 coupler installs that the coupler cage (the metal
part that the shift rod sticks into) is fabricated poorly and DOESN'T FIT
the shift rod. it is just a little too small on the inner diameter.

I have used the new bushings with the old cage that fits, with success.

Good Luck,
Will A.
Atlanta GA
'70 Westy "Rebertha"

